description:
Hi,
I have a geo query who has a weird behavior :
SELECT ?venue ?distance
WHERE {
    {
        SELECT ?venue (bif:st_distance(?geo, ?geoOrig) AS ?distance)
        WHERE {
            {
                SELECT ?geoOrig
                WHERE {

                    <URI> schema:geo ?vGeo .
                    ?vGeo schema:longitude ?vLong .
                    ?vGeo schema:latitude ?vLat .
                    BIND(bif:st_point(xsd:decimal(?vLong), xsd:decimal(?vLat)) as ?geoOrig)

                }
            }
            ?venue a dul:Place .
            ?venue schema:geo ?geoVenue .
            ?geoVenue schema:longitude ?long .
            ?geoVenue schema:latitude ?lat .
            BIND(bif:st_point(xsd:decimal(?long), xsd:decimal(?lat)) as ?geo)

            FILTER(bif:st_distance(?geo, ?geoOrig) <= 0.5) .
        }
    }

}
ORDER BY ASC (?distance)

Give me this error :
Virtuoso 22023 Error GEO..: Function st_point needs a number as argument 1, not an arg of type DB_NULL (204)

And If I remove the last FILTER it works. I cast the values in xsd:decimal and the function tells me, it's not a number. Unless I did something wrong in the query, I think it is a bug.
